{{cleanup-verify}}
'''Ve''' is a [[gender-neutral pronoun]] that has not gained widespread acceptance. The gender neutral pronoun 'Ve' was proposed by New Zealand writer Keri Hulme (winner of the 1985 Booker prize for 'the bone people') some time in the 1980s.
[[Greg Egan]] uses ''ve'' for non-gendered [[artificial intelligence]]s in his novel ''[[Diaspora (novel)|Diaspora]]'', and for "[[asexuality|asex]]" humans in ''[[Distress (novel)|Distress]]''.

